  "rationale": "<p>Rewrite each fraction with the common denominator (<i>x</i> + 4)(2<i>x</i> &minus; 7). The first fraction becomes 3(<i>x</i> + 4)/((<i>x</i> + 4)(2<i>x</i> &minus; 7)) = (3<i>x</i> + 12)/((<i>x</i> + 4)(2<i>x</i> &minus; 7)). The second becomes (2<i>x</i> &minus; 7)/((<i>x</i> + 4)(2<i>x</i> &minus; 7)). Subtracting yields (3<i>x</i> + 12 &minus; 2<i>x</i> + 7)/((<i>x</i> + 4)(2<i>x</i> &minus; 7)) = (<i>x</i> + 19)/((<i>x</i> + 4)(2<i>x</i> &minus; 7)). Choices A, C, and D result from arithmetic or sign errors when combining numerators.</p>",
